## Document Summary: IBM Batch Report for Batch 15, Bangor (NSW)

This document is an "IBM Batch Report" dated June 15, 2016, detailing the processing of Batch Number 15 for the Bangor Vote Collection Point (ID 2178) in NSW, associated with Electoral Event ID 19694. It records the outcome of various automated and manual checks for 50 individual ballots within this batch, identified by unique Ballot IDs (e.g., `19694NSWHUGH012421780015_001` through `_050`).

The report includes detailed columns for checks such as `QualityAssurance Checked`, `Initials Checked`, `Official Mark Checked`, `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Formality Result Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, and various `ATL` (Above-the-Line) and `BTL` (Below-the-Line) preference, mismatch, saved, breakdown, and formal checks. For all 50 ballots listed in this specific report, every check across all categories indicates "OK", signifying successful and formal processing without any identified anomalies or issues.

### Relevance to FOI Request:

This document directly aligns with Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] for 'IBM Outputs', specifically as one of the "IBM Batch Report" PDF files. It provides granular insight into the ballot processing workflow, confirming the structure and content described in the request overview, including batch metadata, electoral event context, and ballot-level formality and preference checks. While the request overview notes frequent "HAS ISSUES" entries in these reports, this particular document serves as an example of a "clean" batch where all processing checks were successfully passed ("OK"). This demonstrates the system's normal operational output when no anomalies are detected, providing a baseline for comparison with reports that do contain "HAS ISSUES" entries and their associated alphanumeric codes.
